Count 2 - Violate Harassment Restraining Order - No contest plea.  Convicted.  State moves to dismiss and read in count 1, bail jumping.  Sentence is withheld.   Defendant is placed on probation to DOC for eighteen (18) months.   Conditions of probation are:
1) Domestic violence assessment and counseling; 
2) Assessment/treatment/counseling as deemed appropriate by the Department's assessment process;
3) Maintain absolute sobriety;
4) Have no contact withthe victim, Linda Louison, defendant must maintain a distance of 500 feet away from the victim.  Defendant must move away within the next 45 days from his current residence.  Exceptions to the no contact are if they victim comes toward him, contact in court for divorce proceedings and incidental contact.  
5) Pay costs of action;
6) Pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined;
7) Attend batterer's treatment group.
$1,000.00 cash bail to be returned to poster.  
Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights.
